revision.text:
{{Documentation subpage}}
{{High-use}}
<!-- Place categories where indicated at the bottom of this page and interwikis at Wikidata -->
Displays a flag icon, country name, and country code in parentheses.  The first input parameter is the three-letter country code, and the second (optional) parameter is the flag variant label, if necessary.  This template is useful for sports results tables, for example, where country codes are often used to identify national teams. Use the optional <code>code</code> parameter when a country name is used to select the flag.

==Examples==
{{nowiki template demo|format=inline|output=nowiki+|code=<nowiki>{{flag team|IRQ}}</nowiki>}}
{{nowiki template demo|format=inline|output=nowiki+|code=<nowiki>{{flag team|SCO}}</nowiki>}}
{{nowiki template demo|format=inline|output=nowiki+|code=<nowiki>{{flag team|GBR}}</nowiki>}}
{{nowiki template demo|format=inline|output=nowiki+|code=<nowiki>{{flag team|CAN|1921}}</nowiki>}}
{{nowiki template demo|format=inline|output=nowiki+|code=<nowiki>{{flag team|FR Yugoslavia|code=YUG}}</nowiki>}}

==See also==
*[[Template:Flag athlete]] for a similar template useful for individual names
*[[Template:Flag]] and [[Template:Flag icon]] for additional discussion about flag variations
*[[List of IOC country codes]] and [[List of FIFA country codes]] for some commonly used country codes

{{Flag templates}}

<includeonly>{{sandbox other||
<!-- Categories below this line and interwikis at Wikidata -->
[[Category:Flag template system]]

}}</includeonly>

